    <section class="py-12 border-b border-terminal-border" id="environment-variables">
      <h3 class="text-terminal-amber mb-6">### environment variables</h3>
      <p class="text-terminal-fg mb-4 text-sm">
        All optional. Environment variables override config.yaml values.
      </p>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-terminal-fg text-xs">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-terminal-border">
              <th class="text-left py-2 px-2">Variable</th>
              <th class="text-left py-2 px-2">Overrides</th>
              <th class="text-left py-2 px-2">Description</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-terminal-border">
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 px-2"><code class="text-terminal-cyan">ENCHANTER_MODEL</code></td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2"><code class="text-terminal-fg">model.default</code></td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2">Model ID to use</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 px-2"><code class="text-terminal-cyan">ENCHANTER_BASE_URL</code></td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2"><code class="text-terminal-fg">model.base_url</code></td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2">API base URL</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 px-2"><code class="text-terminal-cyan">ENCHANTER_API_KEY</code></td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2"><code class="text-terminal-fg">model.api_key</code></td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2">API key (not needed for local providers)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 px-2"><code class="text-terminal-cyan">ENCHANTER_HOME</code></td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2">—</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2">Data directory (default: <code class="text-terminal-fg">~/.enchanter</code>)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 px-2"><code class="text-terminal-cyan">OPENAI_API_KEY</code></td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2">fallback</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2">Used if ENCHANTER_API_KEY is not set</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 px-2"><code class="text-terminal-cyan">OPENAI_BASE_URL</code></td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2">fallback</td>
              <td class="py-2 px-2">Used if ENCHANTER_BASE_URL is not set</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="text-terminal-fg mt-4 text-sm">
        Provider <code class="bg-terminal-dim rounded px-1 py-0.5 text-xs text-terminal-cyan">api_key</code> and <code class="bg-terminal-dim rounded px-1 py-0.5 text-xs text-terminal-cyan">base_url</code> fields
        support <code class="bg-terminal-dim rounded px-1 py-0.5 text-xs text-terminal-cyan">&#36;&#123;VAR&#125;</code> expansion, so you can write
        <code class="bg-terminal-dim rounded px-1 py-0.5 text-xs text-terminal-cyan">api_key: &#36;&#123;OPENROUTER_API_KEY&#125;</code> instead of hardcoding.
      </p>

      <div class="py-4">
        <a href="#" class="text-terminal-dim text-sm hover:text-terminal-green no-underline">↑ back to top</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-12 border-b border-terminal-border" id="data-directory">
